 ===========================================
 KEEP THESE FILES (Do NOT ignore)
 ===========================================
 The following patterns ensure important
 files are NOT ignored even if they match
 patterns above

 Keep template files (these should be committed)
!templates/
!/.template.
!templates//

 Keep environment example files
!.env.example
!.env..example
!/.env.example
!/.env..example

 Keep the main environment files (these contain placeholders, not secrets)
.env.staging
.env.prod
.env.staging.example
.env.prod.example

 Keep documentation
!README.md
!CHANGELOG.md
!LICENSE
!/.md

 Keep configuration files
!requirements.txt
!requirements.yml
!ansible.cfg.example
!Makefile
!Taskfile.yml

 Keep scripts
!.sh
!scripts/
!scripts//

 ===========================================
 ENVIRONMENT SPECIFIC
 ===========================================

 Local testing directories
test-output/
test-results/
.test/

 Ansible Galaxy collections (usually installed globally)
collections/ansible_collections/

 Local inventory files (may contain sensitive IPs)
inventory.local.
hosts.local.

 Dynamic inventory scripts with credentials
inventory_.py
!inventory_example.py
